# Mobile-first CSS (frontend and guides)

## Critical Rules

- **Base styles** target the smallest layout first (narrow / touch). Use **`@media (min-width: …)`** (or shared mixins such as `medium-and-up`) to adjust layout for larger breakpoints.
- **Do not** rely on **`@media (max-width: …)`** as the default way to express mobile-only behavior when **`base + min-width`** can express it. Reserve max-width for rare cases (e.g. capping a one-off hack) and add a short comment explaining why.
- **Reuse** existing breakpoint variables or mixins from the file or `tokens.scss` / shared SCSS instead of new magic pixel values when equivalents exist.
- **Touch targets and mobile polish** live in the narrow default or in min-width-enhanced rules, not in max-width blocks that patch desktop last.

## Examples

<example title="Progressive enhancement with min-width">
  ```scss
  .panel {
    padding: 12px 16px;
  }

  @include medium-and-up {
    .panel {
      padding: 24px 32px;
    }
  }
  ```
</example>

<example type="invalid" title="Max-width-first for the same intent">
  ```scss
  @media (max-width: 959px) {
    .panel {
      padding: 12px 16px;
    }
  }
  ```
</example>
